name: Sunflower
description: Tall, cheerful flower that follows the sun. Great for gardens and cut bouquets.

name: Rose
description: Classic flowering shrub known for its beauty and fragrance. Many varieties available.

name: Lavender
description: Aromatic herb with purple flowers. Drought-tolerant and attracts pollinators.

name: Basil
description: Popular culinary herb with sweet, aromatic leaves. Prefers warm weather.

name: Cactus
description: Low-maintenance desert plant that stores water in its stems. Perfect for beginners.

name: Orchid
description: Exotic flowering plant with delicate blooms. Requires indirect light and humidity.

name: Mint
description: Fast-growing herb with refreshing flavor. Great for teas and garnishes.

name: Tulip
description: Spring-blooming bulb with vibrant cup-shaped flowers. Plant in fall for spring color.

name: Fern
description: Lush green foliage plant that thrives in shady, moist environments.

name: Aloe Vera
description: Succulent with healing gel inside its leaves. Very drought-tolerant.

name: Daisy
description: Simple, cheerful flower with white petals and yellow centers. Easy to grow.

name: Pothos
description: Popular houseplant with trailing vines. Tolerates low light and irregular watering.

name: Cherry Blossom
description: Iconic flowering tree known for its stunning spring blooms.

name: Succulent Mix
description: Assortment of small, colorful succulents. Ideal for desktops and gifts.

name: Peony
description: Luxurious flowering perennial with large, fragrant blooms in late spring.

name: Snake Plant
description: Hardy indoor plant that purifies air and survives neglect.

name: Hydrangea
description: Shrub with large flower clusters that change color based on soil pH.

name: Thyme
description: Low-growing aromatic herb used in cooking and ground cover.

name: Monstera
description: Tropical houseplant with dramatic split leaves. Loves humidity and bright light.

name: Zinnia
description: Bright, long-blooming annual perfect for cutting gardens and attracting butterflies.
